# README maintenance

[README.md](../../README.md) is the **public face of Contraponto** — the first doc visitors and agents read.

## When to update README.md

| Trigger | Action in README |
|---------|------------------|
| New user-facing feature shipped | Add bullet under **Features** (or create subsection) |
| Feature removed or renamed | Update or remove matching bullet |
| Tech stack change | Update **Tech stack** / stack section |
| Dev startup or URLs change | Update **Quick start** commands and links |
| New dev persona in `dev-import.sql` | Update dev login table |
| New top-level doc agents should know | Add row to documentation index |

## What belongs in README vs other docs

| README | Elsewhere |
|--------|-----------|
| One-line pitch, tech stack, quick start | — |
| Feature bullets (what the product does) | [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) for routes, roles, click paths |
| Doc index links | Full detail in linked docs |
| Dev login summary | Full personas in feature-catalog § Dev personas |

Do **not** duplicate route tables in README — link to [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) and [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Finish checklist (user-visible features)

1. Update [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) (routes, steps, § Dev personas).
2. Update [`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql) ([dev-import-sql-safety.mdc](dev-import-sql-safety.mdc)).
3. Update README **Features** section when capability is newsworthy.
4. Update [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) if vocabulary changed.
5. Update `feature/<slug>.md` changelog per [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc).

